			<description><![CDATA[<p>
	Chat Sports is an online media startup based in San Francisco, California. At Chat Sports, we take our audience to a new level by seamlessly delivering personalized sports content via social networking, comprehensive real-time news and elaborate media mashups, all in one place.</p>
<p>
	Our flagship, <a href="http://ChatSports.com">ChatSports.com</a>, was launched in April 2011 and delivers the most extensive sports coverage available for franchises in the NFL, NBA, MLB and NHL as well as NCAA. Chat Sports delivers popular, relevant and personalized content from across the sports landscape for every team it covers directly to our users. Your life as a sports fan just got easier.</p>
<p>
	<strong>Who you are</strong></p>
<p>
	You are a creative-minded college student with a passion for sports who also has a knack for being humorous, insightful and interesting.</p>
<p>
	<strong>What you will do</strong></p>
<p>
	Chat Sports has over 100 exclusive writers that add unique content to our sports news delivery engine, providing a comprehensive sports experience on the web for passionate fans. The Sports Editing Internship will manage and review the content for 25+ writers in our network.</p>
<p>
	To our writers, you will be their writing coach, idea source, fact checker and social media consultant. You will review their content, utilize your editing prowess, provide impactful feedback and help shape Chat Sports&rsquo; social media distribution strategy.</p>
<p>
	All duties of this position are high level and challenging. Almost no clerical, administrative or busy work duties.</p>
<p>
	<strong>Must haves</strong></p>
<p>
	&bull; Amazing organizational skills<br />
	&bull; A creative mind<br />
	&bull; Passion for sports<br />
	&bull; Excellent writing &amp; editorial skills<br />
	&bull; Strong knowledge of the online sports media landscape</p>
<p>
	<strong>Nice to have</strong></p>
<p>
	&bull; Previous writing/editing experience online<br />
	&bull; Experience creating and maintaining a personal blog<br />
	&bull; Basic HTML skills<br />
	&bull; Social media ninja-like abilities<br />
	&bull; Journalism coursework</p>
<p>
	<strong>What is in it for you?</strong></p>
<p>
	&bull; Experience working with senior staff at a growing media company<br />
	&bull; Course credit with schools approval<br />
	&bull; Challenging work environment and interaction with the latest online technology<br />
	&bull; Opportunity to turn creative ideas into a product<br />
	&bull; Potential for full-time employment upon graduation</p>
